The Bauchi State Police Command said it killed two suspected kidnappers and robbers, destroyed their camp and recovered series of exhibits in Alkaleri Local Government Area of the state. In a statement yesterday, its spokesperson, Kamal Abubakar, said the criminals were killed on Tuesday during an operation aimed at checking the menace of hoodlums in the state. He said: “On September 24, based on credible intelligence, the command’s team attached to Operation Puff Adder, in collaboration with Danga security volunteers, trailed some kidnap and robbery suspects to their camp in Gali forest, in the said LGA. “On sighting the police team, the suspects engaged them in a gun duel but were successfully overpowered. Two of the suspects were gunned down while the rest were believed to have escaped with bullets wounds. The suspects were taken to Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Teaching Hospital for treatment but were later certified dead by medical doctor.’’ The command also said exhibits recovered during the operation included two AK-47 rifles, 11 rounds of live ammunition and four motorcycles.